miscConds.notes: plus 10% restitution surcharge.  To be determined within 90 days.

No contact with PC, DE, RE, RL, BS, or Azura Healthcare or victim families.  No contact with BP without agent approval.  Not to consume, use or possess any alcohol, illegal drugs, non-prescribed drugs or drug paraphernalia.  No entry into bars, taverns or liquor stores.  Not to be in a vehicle transporting alochol and not have alcohol in residence.  Not to possess anyone else's personal identifying information or documents except for own and daughter's.  Not to work with elderly patients or clients.

Submit DNA sample.  Any counseling, treatment or programming per agent.  Participate and successfully complete treatment court.  Comply with DHS conditions.    Must give a complete and truthful statement about any illegal activity within her knowledge.  To the extent the statement implicates her in any further illegal drug activity, the State would agree not to issue charges.  Must testify truthfully in any proceedings against any implicated individuals.  Truthfulness in her statement and/or testimony would be subject to an Eau Claire Police Department polygraph if the State deems necessary.
AODA and follow through with recommendations.

timeConds.notes: of which the last 10 months of jail sentence are stayed per discretion of agent and treatment court.  30 days may be served as 240 hours of community service.  Community service not to begin until after the restitution is paid in full.  Huber privileges granted for treatment court approved activities.
